docs {
  # Prime Video API Test Suite

  This collection contains 10 comprehensive API endpoint tests for Prime Video using Bruno.

  ## Test Cases

  | # | Test | Method | Purpose |
  |---|------|--------|---------|
  | 1 | GET - Home Page | GET | Test main collection page loads correctly |
  | 2 | GET - Collection Data | GET | Verify collection data API endpoint |
  | 3 | POST - Search Content | POST | Test search content endpoint |
  | 4 | GET - Check Headers | GET | Validate HTTP security headers |
  | 5 | HEAD - Check Availability | HEAD | Verify resource availability |
  | 6 | GET - Cache Behavior | GET | Test cache control behavior |
  | 7 | GET - Invalid Path | GET | Test error handling for invalid paths |
  | 8 | OPTIONS - Allowed Methods | OPTIONS | Check allowed HTTP methods |
  | 9 | GET - Content Encoding | GET | Test content encoding/compression |
  | 10 | GET - Response Consistency | GET | Verify consistent responses |

  ## Features

  - ✅ Support for multiple HTTP methods (GET, HEAD, POST, OPTIONS)
  - ✅ Environment variables for base URLs
  - ✅ Assertions for status codes and headers
  - ✅ Comprehensive test cases with multiple assertions
  - ✅ Performance testing (response time checks)
  - ✅ Security header validation
  - ✅ Content encoding verification
  - ✅ Error handling tests

  ## Environment Setup

  The collection uses production environment variables:
  - `base_url`: https://www.primevideo.com
  - `api_base`: https://api.primevideo.com
  - `content_api`: https://atcglobal-eu-west-1.primevideo.com
  - `timeout`: 30000ms

  ## Running Tests

  1. Import this collection into Bruno
  2. Select the "production" environment
  3. Run all tests or individual tests
  4. View results in Bruno's test runner

  ## Expected Results

  All tests should pass with:
  - Status codes: 200, 204, 301, 302, 404 (depending on test)
  - Response times under 10 seconds (typically < 5s)
  - Valid HTTP headers present
  - Expected content in responses
}
